# @param {Integer[]} nums
# @return {Boolean}
def can_traverse_all_pairs(nums)
    n = nums.length
    parent = Array.new(n) { |i| i }

    def find(parent, x)
        return x if parent[x] == x
        parent[x] = find(parent, parent[x])
        parent[x]
    end

    def union(parent, x, y)
        px = find(parent, x)
        py = find(parent, y)
        parent[px] = py if px != py
    end

    # Sieve of Eratosthenes to find all primes up to the max number in nums
    max_num = nums.max
    primes = Array.new(max_num + 1) { |i| i }
    (2..Math.sqrt(max_num)).each do |i|
        if primes[i] == i
            (i*i).step(max_num, i) do |j|
                primes[j] = i if primes[j] == j
            end
        end
    end

    # Map each prime to a unique index in nums
    prime_to_index = {}
    nums.each_with_index do |num, i|
        # Factorize the number and union its prime factors
        while num > 1
            prime_factor = primes[num]
            if prime_to_index[prime_factor]
                union(parent, i, prime_to_index[prime_factor])
            else
                prime_to_index[prime_factor] = i
            end
            num /= prime_factor while num % prime_factor == 0
        end
    end

    # Check if all elements are connected
    root = find(parent, 0)
    (1...n).all? { |i| find(parent, i) == root }
end
